Aldar Properties, Arabtec Holding and Depa: Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-03-07T05:34:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/aldar-properties-arabtec-holding-and-depa-gulf-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Persian Gulf markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are from the last close.  The Dubai Financial Market General Index advanced 2.7
percent. Saudi Arabia’s  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  jumped 0.9
percent.  Arabtec Holding PJSC (ARTC UH): The biggest publicly traded
construction company in the  United Arab Emirates  said the board
will meet tomorrow to review proposals to sell convertible bonds
and raise capital through a rights offer. The shares surged 3.5
percent to 1.20 dirhams.        Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR)  :  Abu Dhabi ’s biggest
developer said its 2.8 billion dirhams ($762 million) of
convertible bonds will pay an interest rate of 4 percent a year.
The securities will be sold to Mubadala Development Co. The
shares rose 3.9 percent to 1.32 dirhams.    Depa Ltd. (DEPA)  : The interior design contractor that
fitted out the world’s tallest tower in Dubai said 2010 profit
will be “significantly impacted” due a claim related to the
Burj Khalifa contract. The shares were unchanged at $0.659.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
